# YOU BECOME WHAT YOU READ · a message of PHONETIKOS

a message-emergent of the PHN universe — the message · the canon shapes the container — aggregately, and both ways. moniker ⟦YOU BECOME WHAT YOU READ:PHN:34251e⟧

**who —** a probabilistic cast, not a stamp — ‘this kind of story, repeated, will shape this kind of container — more than likely.’
**what —** YOU BECOME WHAT YOU READ — the transitive, aggregate law that a repeated canon casts a matching container: Clancy readers skew martial, fantasy/D&D readers skew that mould, a kid raised on neutral-AI sci-fi gets a neutral-mind container.
**where —** every reader's shelf, where a steady diet of one kind of story leaves a matching cast on the mind
**why —** because the nurture and cultural-globe layers of the Idiolect Stack don't only shape the voice — the stories you repeat shape the whole container: what you find salient, admirable, normal.
**how —** repeated immersion in a genre transports and cultivates — its assumptions quietly become your defaults — while the self you already are selects which canon to invest in; the two co-author each other.

**the seal —** You become what you read — more than likely; and you read what you were already becoming. The canon and the container co-author each other.

> a catalogued message under the DLW standard — honestly sourced; the paper marks what is
> established, what is model, and what is symbol in its Real-or-Fluff.

